## Summary Table

| Severity | Count | Key Areas |
|----------|-------|-----------|
| 🔴 Critical | 5 | Concurrency/thread safety, data loss |
| 🟠 High | 9 | Sync reliability, alarm delivery, architecture |
| 🟡 Medium | 12 | Maintainability, localization, code duplication |
| 🟢 Low | 10 | Style, dead code, minor UX |
| **Total** | **36** | |

## Recommended Priority Order

1. **Fix all Critical concurrency issues first** (C-1 through C-4) — these cause crashes in production
2. **Address C-5** (session data loss) — users lose sleep data
3. **Fix H-5, H-6, H-9** — alarm reliability is the core product
4. **Surface H-1** (scheduling errors to UI) — users need to know their alarm failed
5. **Refactor H-4** (God method) — prerequisite for safely fixing other payload bugs
6. **Address M-4** (placeholder URLs) — legal requirement before App Store submission
7. Everything else in severity order
